# Requirements Rationale Tools

## Requirements

- Project context: E-commerce retention analysis for a portfolio case study.
- Project dataset: Orders, customers, support tickets, and campaign touchpoints.
- Project goals: Show churn insight, segmentation, and a reproducible technical workflow.
- Prefer free deploy: Yes

## Thinking

- Framework chosen: CRISP-DM
  - Why: Goals are insight-first, so the project should emphasize business framing, analysis, and recommendations.
- Layer chosen: Pro
  - Why: Goals need balanced domain insight and technical depth, which fits the middle tier best.
- Tool chosen: RAWGraphs
  - Why: Free deployment is the priority, so a browser-first and static-friendly visualization path is the safer default.
  - Deploy note: RAWGraphs fits static portfolio publishing much better than Superset.

## Tools

- SQL: Required
- Python: Required
- Visualization: RAWGraphs

## Delivery Steps

1. inspect dataset and define data quality risks
2. write SQL transformations and analysis queries
3. add Python work when the selected layer requires it
