# Project Overview PDR

## Overview

Build an open-source kit for Codex agents that generates professional data visualization portfolio projects in isolated folders.

## Product Goal

- help users show domain knowledge
- help users show technical knowledge
- produce repeatable, git-ready project workspaces

## Core User Flow

1. clone repo
2. run kit command
3. answer intake questions
4. receive generated project folder under `projects/`
5. refine and commit the generated workspace

## Core Requirements

- workflow-first orchestration
- thin entrypoints
- mandatory hooks
- agent-scoped execution
- one framework owner per generated project
- one visualization layer per generated project
- one visualization tool per generated project

## Constraints

- default free-deploy path should prefer `RAWGraphs`
- project outputs must include SQL and/or Python work
- no hardcoded business values in the kit itself
</file>

